Instructions for restaurant manager:

-to use this project we using local docker n8n container
 and if needed there is option for free local llm through
 docker.


1. install docker desktop (for free n8n) and ngrok (to publish n8n)
2. go in cmd navigate(cd) to docker-compose dir of n8n, and run "docker compose up"
   if you dont have OPENAI_KEY do the same process as n8n docker-compose but now
   navigate to ollama docker-compose dir and run the command.
   after in terminal of the project write this command to pull
   the ollama3.8b model run:   docker exec ollama ollama pull llama3:8b.
3.install requirements.txt in Terminal: py -m pip install -r requirements.txt
4.open ngrok and publish the port commands: ngrok config add-authtoken {your_ngrok_key}.
                                            ngrok http {port_number}. (our port is 5678)

5.import from file this 3 json files of n8n:
-tlg_bot:               on tlg_bot.json
-send_events_id_pc:     on send_events&id_pc.json
-get_order_details_pc:  on get_order_details_pc.json

6.create input_python_data table on get_order_details_pc
7.create event_ids table on send_events_id_pc

8.run the restaurant_gradio.py